  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A student is creating a chatbot for their school's website to help answer frequently asked questions. They want to implement natural language processing to help the chatbot better understand and respond to user input. As part of this process, they need to identify the parts of speech in user input to determine the user's intent and generate an appropriate response.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** Write the method <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getWordWithPart()</code> in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Chatbot</code> class to return a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">String</code> containing the parameter <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">currentWord</code> tagged with its part of speech.\r\n\r\n1. Traverse the 1D array <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">partsOfSpeech</code>.\r\n\r\n2. Compare the substring containing the word with <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">currentWord</code>.\r\n\r\n3. If they match, return a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">String</code> containing the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">currentWord</code> concatenated with the substring containing the part of speech. \r\n\t- If the word appears more than once in the array, return the last matching part of speech found.\r\n    - If <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">currentWord</code> is not found, return an empty string.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** Write the method <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">tagPartsOfSpeech()</code> in the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Chatbot</code> class to return a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">String</code> containing the words from <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">statement</code> tagged with their parts of speech. The <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">tagPartsOfSpeech()</code> method should:\r\n\r\n1. Use the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getWordWithPart()</code> method to search for each word in <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">statement</code>. \r\n\t- Matching should be case-sensitive, so only exact matches from the dataset will return a result.\r\n    - If a word is not in the dataset, skip it (_do not include it in the result_)\r\n    - When a word appears more than once in partsOfSpeech, return the _last_ matching entry\r\n\r\n2. Return a <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">String</code> containing each word tagged with its part of speech on separate lines (for example, <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">\"dog: noun\"</code>).\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #3:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">ChatbotRunner</code> class, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">tagPartsOfSpeech()</code> method and print the result.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Check out the documentation for the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">String</code> class in the <strong>Documentation</strong> tab ⬆️ for help with using the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">indexOf()</code> and <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">substring()</code> methods.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<details style=\"background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;\">\r\n    <summary style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: bold;\">🔦 Need help with your algorithm?</summary>\r\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\">\r\n    <p>Here is one approach to solving the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getWordWithPart()</code> method.</p>\r\n        <pre style=\"background-color: #333333; color: white;\">\r\ncreate an empty String for the result\r\n&nbsp;\r\nfor each element in partsOfSpeech\r\n   find the location of the colon\r\n   get the substring containing the characters after the colon\r\n   \r\n   if currentWord equals the word\r\n      get the substring containing the characters from 0 to colon\r\n      concatenate currentWord + \": \" + part of speech\r\n&nbsp;\r\nreturn result\r\n</pre>\r\n    <p>Here is one approach to solving the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">tagPartsOfSpeech()</code> method.</p>\r\n        <pre style=\"background-color: #333333; color: white;\">\r\ncreate an empty String for the result\r\nfind the first location of the space\r\n&nbsp;\r\nwhile location of space does not equal -1\r\n   get the current word from index 0 to the space\r\n   getWordForPart(currentWord)\r\n   \r\n   if length of result returned is greater than 0\r\n      concatenate the result returned to result plus new line\r\n&nbsp;\r\n   update statement to location of the space + 1\r\n   find the location of the next space\r\n&nbsp;\r\nreturn result\r\n</pre>\r\n    </div>\r\n</details>",
